commit.message:
Revert "CI: Add JRuby"

Temporally disable JRuby tests to merge #73

This reverts commit 3c372c7ce564d8e899020b9da3822b14626971e5.

spec: Use appropriate encoding to check request_url & status

In CRuby, they are ASCII_8BIT since they are created by rb_str_new().
On the other hand, they are UTF-8 in JRuby.

Fix the following failed test on JRuby:

  4) HTTP::Parser should parse request: utf-8 path request
     Failure/Error: expect(@parser.send("request_url")).to eq(test["request_url"].force_encoding(Encoding::BINARY))

       expected: "/\xCE\xB4\xC2\xB6/\xCE\xB4t/pope?q=1#narf"
            got: "/δ¶/δt/pope?q=1#narf"

       (compared using ==)
     # ./spec/parser_spec.rb:387:in `block in <main>'

Although they should use same encoding, I don't fix it for now to keep
backward compatibility.

commit.message:
CI: Migrate from Travis CI to GitHub Actions

Because the billing plan of Travis CI has been changed.

https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/billing-overview/
https://blog.travis-ci.com/2021-05-07-orgshutdown

In addition, GitHub Actions has a high affinity to GitHub.

Check value passed to set_header_value_type

This method converts the given symbol to a string, and then compares it
against several literals using ==. This works on JRuby 1.7 but not for
some users on JRuby 9. I'm replacing this with List.contains() and a
constant list of the acceptable values, to both clarify the logic, and
to make the code work on recent JRuby releases.
